15/03/2006
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Montenegrin Parliament Speaker Ranko Krivokapic noted the importance of thorough monitoring of the independence referendum process, during a meeting with the OSCE Permanent Council ambassadors in Podgorica on Tuesday (14 March). The OSCE delegation visited the capital as part of a several-day visit to Serbia-Montenegro. Krivokapic reiterated the Montenegrin authorities' determination to organise the 21 May poll in full compliance with European standards. (Mina, Tanjug - 14/03/06)
